cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Running Qwen 3.6-35B-A3B on DGX Spark with Atlas for Local Speed and Smarts Benchmarks"
message: "If you use this setup, benchmark wrappers, or comparison data, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Rawat"
    given-names: "Rajendra Singh"
    affiliation: "cogni.chat"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0007-5017-1341"
repository-code: "https://github.com/airawatraj/dgx-spark-qwen-super-agent"
abstract: >-
  A lightweight technical implementation and benchmarking suite for running
  RedHatAI/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-NVFP4 on NVIDIA DGX Spark through the Atlas runtime.
  This repository documents the local model-cache layout required by Atlas,
  provides reproducible benchmark wrappers for speed, smarts, and arena-style
  throughput testing, and tracks side-by-side comparison points against a prior
  Nemotron DGX Spark run.
keywords:
  - "Qwen"
  - "DGX Spark"
  - "Atlas"
  - "AI Agents"
  - "NVFP4"
  - "Performance Benchmarking"
license: MIT
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-05-23"